---------------------------------
Installation (on Debian/Ubuntu)
---------------------------------

1. Pidgin
==========

Download and extract the newest pidgin source

# aptitude install libgtk2.0-dev libgstreamer0.10-dev libgtkspell-dev libdbus-glib-1-dev libgnutls-dev libxss-dev libmeanwhile-dev libgadu-dev libnss3-dev tcl8.4-dev tk8.4-dev libltdl3-dev libperl-dev libstartup-notification0-dev libzephyr-dev libxml2-dev libebook1.2-dev libedata-book1.2-dev libcamel1.2-dev libxml-parser-perl libncursesw5-dev libsasl2-dev libsilc-1.1-2-dev libavahi-compat-howl-dev doxygen

Note: Not all libraries are necessary!

$ cd pidgin-*
$ ./configure
$ make
# make install

run pidgin

2. Pidgin-Paranoia
===================

Get it from svn:
$ svn co https://pidgin-paranoia.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/pidgin-paranoia/trunk pidgin-paranoia

$ cd pidgin-paranoia
$ ./autogen.sh
$ ./configure
$ make
# make install

Done. Activate it in the pidgin plug-in menu.

To see the debug messages of the plugin run pidgin like that:

$ pidgin -d | grep paranoia


uninstall: (who wants to do that anyway? ;) )
$ cd pidgin-paranoia
# make uninstall


